# Nuxt Runtime Restart Check

After finishing any substantial task in this repo, always verify the app does not fail with:

`Package import specifier "#internal/nuxt/paths" is not defined ... .nuxt/dist/server/server.mjs`

## Required post-task check

1. Check dev-server output for this exact error.
2. If present, perform a clean dev restart:
   - stop conflicting Nuxt/node processes (`3000`, `24678`);
   - remove `.nuxt` and `.output`;
   - start `npm run dev` again.
3. Re-check target route (or at least `/dashboard`) and confirm no `#internal/nuxt/paths` error.

## Quick fix command

Use this recovery sequence when the error appears:

```bash
lsof -nP -iTCP:3000 -sTCP:LISTEN; lsof -nP -iTCP:24678 -sTCP:LISTEN
kill <pid...>
rm -rf .nuxt .output
npm run dev
```
